lenders.name: Julianne
lenders.occupational_info: I currently work at Boston Health Care For The Homeless Program as a Patient Benefits Coordinator and absolutely love every minute of it.  In the past, I have served with the Jesuit Volunteer Corps (a volunteer corps similar to the PeaceCorps, only with the Jesuit ideology built into our service experience), working in an inner-city low income afterschool program with children ages 5-12, helping them to build the principles of leadership in their every day life to promote well-being, self-sufficiency and confidence.  As a Jesuit Volunteer, we lived in community, did social justice work, explored spirituality, and were dedicated to living in simplicity.  It was an amazing experience. Before that, I went to Hamilton College and majored in biochemistry and classics.  All these experiences have only further enriched my passion for helping others and inspiring the building of community among us all.
